In article <2224@rwing.UUCP> pat@rwing.UUCP (Pat Myrto) writes:
> > The quotes which Ed gives, although not substantially
> > misleading, are simply not correct, and it is easy to draw certain
> > incorrect conclusions from his article.
> They are not misleading, but are not correct.

They are not _substantially_ misleading. They are misleading in a
tangential manner which could easily cause people to draw certain
incorrect conclusions from Ed's comments based on those quotes. I
believe that readers who draw such conclusions deserve a warning, even
though I cannot explain the reasons for the warning at this time.

> Perhaps you can tell us, if it is true that us commoners cannot know what
> we are and are not bound by, how in hell people are supposed to follow
> the law?

That's a very good question. Keep it in mind.

